        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(memory): unify sessions and add associative memory backfill",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nOpenClaw's agent memory work needed a durable, navigable conversational store that survives transcript cleanup, can organize turns into topic boxes, and can safely surface that structure in Control UI without fragmenting one agent across many disconnected chat sessions. The memory backfill and tuning work also needed a repeatable path to seed existing transcript history and lock recall-safe accordion defaults from real usage evidence.\n\nThis PR unifies the Control UI onto the agent main session, adds the durable turns/spans/boxes and associative memory layers, exposes topic accordion controls in the UI/gateway, adds a backfill command, and locks the Phase 4 accordion constants to the approved zero-intersection shape.\n\n## Summary\n- Adds unified Control UI session plumbing so the UI can join `agent:{agentId}:main`.\n- Adds durable conversational-memory turns/spans/boxes, topic accordion UI and gateway controls, associative context/tag/entity traversal, and memory backfill CLI support.\n- Locks Phase 4 / 04-04 Task 3 accordion constants to the approved gemini-1 zero-intersection shape.\n- Rebased cleanly on current `upstream/main`; unrelated local Code Farm commits from the older worktree branch are excluded.\n\n## Evidence\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/memory src/gateway/server-methods/accordion.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-history-budget.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat-history-omission-request.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/topic-accordion.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-gateway.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-render.helpers.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/app-lifecycle-connect.node.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/associative-ranking.test.ts src/commands/memory-backfill.test.ts`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- PR CI started; the initial `Real behavior proof` failure was this PR-body policy check, addressed by adding this section.\n\n## Phase 4 Constant-Lock Evidence\n- Real main-history checkpoint ran against an isolated temp `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`; live main DB was not mutated.\n- Dataset: 2,061 turns / 2,014 spans / 77 boxes.\n- Baseline: 27 recall failures, 14.9% savings, thrash 14.\n- Locked gemini-1: 26 recall failures, 14.9% savings, thrash 11.\n- Locked values: `mode=zero-intersection`, `activeWindowTurns=12`, `zeroIntersectionDwellTurns=5`, `activeSetCardinalityFloor=2`.\n\n## Notes\n- The full `pnpm build`/Crabbox gate is intentionally left to PR CI because local Crabbox is unavailable on this machine.\n",
